3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FThavisin%2Fstatus%2F1788135429793054722%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Srettha%20Thavisin%20called%20on%20the%20country's%20Ministry%20of%20Public%20Health%20to%20revise%20its%20list%20of%20illegal%20substances%20to%20once%20again%20include%20cannabis%2C%20and%20to%20publish%20new%20guidelines%20limiting%20its%20use%20for%20medical%20and%20health%20purposes%20only.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThavisin%20also%20urged%20Thailand's%20health%20and%20justice%20ministries%20to%20join%20forces%20to%20arrest%20those%20who%20escape%20drug%20treatment%20or%20fail%20to%20undergo%20treatment%2C%20in%20order%20to%20prosecute%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrugs%20are%20a%20problem%20that%20destroys%20the%20future%20of%20the%20nation%2C%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20government%20agencies%20need%20to%20work%20together%20to%20eradicate%20drug%20activity%20and%20show%20clear%20progress%20within%2090%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThailand%20was%20the%20first%20Southeast%20Asian%20country%20to%20legalize%20medical%20cannabis%20in%202018%2C%20and%20the%20first%20Asian%20country%20to%20decriminalize%20recreational%20cannabis%20in%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fdariosabaghi%2F2022%2F01%2F27%2Fthailand-has-become-the-first-asian-country-to-decriminalize-recreational-cannabis%2F%3Fsh%3D2e4c54534b21%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Forbes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20country's%20former%20health%20minister%2C%20Anutin%20Charnvirakul%2C%20spearheaded%20the%20effort%20in%202022%2C%20announcing%20his%20ministry%20would%20give%20away%20one%20million%20cannabis%20plants%20to%20Thai%20households%20for%20license-free%20cultivation%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20drug%20was%20removed%20from%20the%20country's%20list%20of%20controlled%20substances%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F05%2F12%2Fworld%2Fasia%2Fthailand-legal-weed-plant.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20since%20taking%20power%20last%20August%2C%20Thavisin%20has%20made%20clear%20his%20intention%20to%20overhaul%20the%20country's%20drug%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20party%20ran%20on%20an%20anti-drug%20platform%2C%20pledging%20to%20eradicate%20drugs%20from%20Thai%20society%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F6316295%2Fthailand-cannabis-restrictions-srettha%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20Time%20magazine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Fvideos%2F2023-09-21%2Fthai-pm-aims-to-regulate-cannabis-for-medical-use-only%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterview%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Bloomberg%20in%20September%2C%20Thavisin%20said%20Thailand%20needed%20to%20regulate%20cannabis%20because%20the%20country%20has%20a%20%26quot%3Bwidespread%26quot%3B%20drug%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20countries%20have%20legalized%20or%20decriminalized%20cannabis%20for%20recreational%20use%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20including%20Canada%2C%20Germany%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20South%20Africa.%20In%20the%20US%2C%2024%20states%2C%20two%20territories%2C%20and%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia%20have%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncsl.org%2Fcivil-and-criminal-justice%2Fcannabis-overview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegalized%3C%2Fa%3E%20small%20amounts%20of%20cannabis%20for%20adult%20recreational%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20global%20cannabis%20market%20was%20worth%20about%20%2445%20billion%2C%20and%20it%20could%20be%20worth%20more%20than%20%24101%20billion%20by%202026%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprohibitionpartners.com%2Freports%2Fthe-global-cannabis-report-edition-3%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DData%2520Packages-%2COverview%2CUS%2524101%2520billion%2520by%25202026.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimates%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Prohi