enough.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20tech%20is%20still%20in%20its%20early%20stages%20and%20expensive%2C%20ranging%20from%20%24600%20to%20%241%2C000%20per%20ton%20of%20carbon.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20startup%20Climeworks%20this%20week%20switched%20on%20the%20largest%20direct-air-capture%20plant%2C%20which%20pulls%20carbon%20dioxide%20from%20the%20sky%20and%20locks%20it%20away%20underground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClimeworks%20said%20the%20plant%2C%20called%20Mammoth%2C%20has%20about%2010%20times%20the%20capacity%20of%20its%20first%20facility%20and%20could%20capture%20up%20to%2036%2C000%20metric%20tons%20of%20carbon%20emissions%20a%20year%20once%20it's%20completed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20amount%20is%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalcarbonbudget.org%2Ffossil-co2-emissions-at-record-high-in-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20more%20than%2040%20billion%20metric%20tons%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimated%20to%20have%20been%20emitted%20globally%20in%202023%2C%20but%20the%20opening%20of%20Mammoth%20in%20Iceland%20marks%20a%20milestone%20for%20a%20nascent%20technology%20that%20scientists%20say%20will%20be%20key%20to%20slowing%20the%20climate%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECountries%20that%20signed%20the%202015%20Paris%20Agreement%20said%20they%20would%20keep%20global%20temperatures%20from%20rising%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20above%20preindustrial%20levels.%20A%20UN%20science%20panel%20has%20warned%20that%20the%20risk%20of%20catastrophic%20climate%20effects%20%E2%80%94%20including%20deadly%20heat%20waves%2C%20drought%2C%20famine%2C%20and%20infectious%20diseases%20%E2%80%94%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipcc.ch%2Freport%2Fsixth-assessment-report-cycle%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20increases%20with%20each%20degree%20of%20warming%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20planet-warming%20emissions%20have%20continued%20to%20rise.%20The%20Global%20Carbon%20Project%20estimated%20that%20these%20emissions%20reached%20record%20levels%20in%202023%2C%20mainly%20driven%20by%20burning%20fossil%20fuels%20like%20oil%2C%20gas%2C%20and%20coal%20for%20energy%20and%20transportation.%20European%20climate%20scientists%20on%20Wednesday%20said%20April%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimate.copernicus.eu%2Fcopernicus-global-temperature-record-streak-continues-april-2024-was-hottest-record%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewas%20the%20hottest%20month%20on%20record%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20continuing%20an%2011-month%20streak.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECountries%20and%20companies%20aren't%20slashing%20emissions%20fast%20enough%2C%20so%20technology%20like%20direct%20air%20capture%20is%20becoming%20more%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20an%20expensive%20and%20uncertain%20pathway.%20Analysts%20estimate%20that%20for%20direct%20air%20capture%20to%20be%20widely%20adopted%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fagenda%2F2023%2F08%2Fhow-to-get-direct-air-capture-under-150-per-ton-to-meet-net-zero-goals%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20price%20of%20removing%20and%20storing%201%20ton%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20have%20to%20fall%20to%20%24100%20by%202050.%20Today%20it%20ranges%20from%20%24600%20to%20%241%2C000.%20Climateworks'%20Mammoth%20plant%20also%20cost%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20to%20build%2C%20though%20the%20company%20didn't%20disclose%20the%20exact%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%2C%20which%20has%20big-name%20customers%20including%20Microsoft%2C%20Shopify%2C%20Swiss%20Re%2C%20Stripe%2C%20and%20JPMorgan%20Chase%2C%20said%20cost%20reduction%20was%20a%20priority.%20It%20added%20that%20while%20the%20Mammoth%20project%20wouldn't%20achieve%20that%2C%20it%20would%20help%20it%20innovate%20further%20and%20make%20the%20technology%20more%20efficient%20as%20it%20scales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClimeworks%20aims%20to%20become%20large%20enough%20to%20remove%201%20million%20metric%20tons%20of%20carbon%20a%20year%20by%202030%20and%201%20billion%20metric%20tons%20by%202050%20%E2%80%94%20or%20a%20megaton%20and%20gigaton.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClimeworks'%20operations%20in%20Iceland%20are%20powered%20by%20renewable%20geothermal%20energy.%20In%20a%20press%20call%2C%20Jan%20Wurzbacher%2C%20a%20cofounder%20and%20co-CEO%20of%20Climeworks%2C%20described%20the%20process%3A%20Fans%20draw%20air%20through%20filters%20to%20separate%20out%20the%20carbon%20dioxide%2C%20which%20is%20then%20compressed%20with%20water%20and%20pushed%20underground%20into%20basalt%20rock%20formations.%20Within%20two%20years%20the%20mixture%20turns%20into%20rock%20and%20is%20stored%20away%20for%20millions%20of%20years.%20In%20early%202023%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcarbon-dioxide-removal-air-sky-machine-climate-change-climeworks-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindependent%20third%20party%20verified%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20process%20and%20its%20results%20were%20sound.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20more%20needed%20to%20scale%20up%20this%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20Wurzbacher%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20about%20offtake.%20It's%20about%20markets%2C%20standards%2C%20and%20regulations.%20And%20it's%20about%20public%20and%20private%20funding.%20A%20lot%20is%20needed%20in%20that%20area%2C%20and%20we%20need%20to%20move%20forward%20quickly%20to%20reach%20our%20targets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWurzbacher%20said%20Climeworks%20had%20projects%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20development%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Canada%2C%20Norway%2C%20Oman%2C%20and%20Kenya.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Energy%20last%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Farticles%2Fbiden-harris-administration-announces-12-billion-nations-first-direct-air-capture%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%20%241.2%20billion%20in%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20direct-air-capture%20demonstration%20plants.%20Climeworks%20is%20involved%20in%20a%20project%20in%20Louisiana%2C%20while%20Occidental%20Petroleum%20was%20selected%20for%20a%20plant%20in%20West%20Texas.%20The%20two%20plants%20could%20remove%20more%20than%202%20million%20metric%20tons%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20from%20the%20air%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworlds-largest-carbon-removal-plant-iceland-climeworks-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715261106000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663cca7e9686a6f37bfd8953%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworlds-largest-carbon-removal-plant-iceland-climeworks-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Climate%20tech%20like%20carbon%20removal%20is%20becoming%20more%20important%20because%20the%20world%20isn't%20cutting%20emissions%20fast%20enough.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cboudreau%40insider.com%20(Catherine%20Boudreau)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworlds-largest-carbon-removal-plant-iceland-climeworks-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ha%20Joon-Ryeo%20Won's%20chemistry%20goes%20VIRAL%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715261064000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109984937%2Cimgsize-36036.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fkorean%2Fwi-ha-joon-and-jung-ryeo-wons-fiery-chemistry-during-the-midnight-romance-in-hangwon-promotions-goes-viral-watch-video%2Farticleshow%2F109984845.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F109984845.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EWi%20Ha%20Joon%20and%20Jung%20Ryeo%20Won's%20press%20conference%20reenactment%20generates%20online%20buzz%2C%20with%20fans%20eagerly%20awaiting%20the%20premiere.%20Candid%20photos%20showcase%20their%20chemis