0opening%20savings%20accounts%20for%20her%20grandchildren.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EShe%20taught%20me%20from%20a%20young%20age%20that%20life%20insurance%20is%20a%20valuable%20tool%20that%20can%20help%20your%20family.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20shows%20that%20most%20of%20our%20habits%20around%20money%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F01926187.2014.935684%23.VO-XOXzF_Td%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eformed%20by%20age%209%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20a%20mother%20of%20three%20young%20children%2C%20one%20of%20my%20goals%20is%20to%20help%20my%20kids%20develop%20healthy%20financial%20habits%20from%20a%20young%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20desire%20to%20raise%20financially%20savvy%20adults%20has%20made%20me%20reflect%20on%20the%20money%20lessons%20I%20learned%20from%20my%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20the%20ones%20I%20learned%20from%20my%20mother%2C%20who%20died%20in%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20my%20mother%20didn't%20share%20a%20ton%20of%20financial%20concepts%20with%20me.%20However%2C%20she%20shared%20a%20few%20valuable%20pieces%20of%20advice%20about%20money%20using%20real-life%20examples.%20She%20was%20also%20intentional%20about%20repeating%20those%20stories%20to%20my%20siblings%20and%20me%20over%20the%20years.%20Here%20are%20some%20of%20the%20lessons%20about%20money%20I%20learned%20from%20my%20mother.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Budgeting%20a%20percentage%20of%20my%20income%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20about%2010%20years%20old%2C%20my%20mother%20started%20talking%20to%20me%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-budgeting-apps%5C%22%3Ebudgeting%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20living%20below%20your%20means%2C%20and%20setting%20aside%20at%20least%2020%20to%2030%25%20of%20your%20money.%20She%20emphasized%20the%20importance%20of%20having%20money%20available%20just%20in%20case%20because%20unexpected%20things%20always%20happen%20in%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mother%20used%20to%20share%20examples%20of%20how%20practicing%20those%20habits%20helped%20her%20accomplish%20things%20in%20her%20life%20and%20how%20not%20practicing%20those%20habits%20was%20detrimental.%20At%2013%20years%20old%2C%20I%20created%20my%20first%20budget%20to%20make%20sure%20I%20put%20away%20at%20least%2020%25%20of%20my%20allowance.%20Budgeting%20is%20a%20habit%20that%20I%20developed%20as%20a%20teen%20and%20carried%20well%20into%20adulthood%2C%20and%20I%20still%20practice%20it%20today%20in%20my%20late%2030s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Waiting%20before%20making%20unplanned%20purchases%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mother%20never%20made%20any%20large%2C%20unplanned%2C%20optional%20purchases.%20When%20we%20were%20on%20vacation%2C%20my%20mother%20would%20have%20a%20shopping%20budget%20for%20the%20trip.%20She%20didn't%20make%20any%20significant%20purchases%20without%20taking%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20to%20think%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20asking%20my%20mother%20why%20she%20wouldn't%20buy%20things%20that%20she%20wanted%20since%20she%20had%20the%20money%20for%20them.%20She%20would%20say%20that%20being%20able%20to%20afford%20something%20is%20not%20a%20good%20enough%20reason%20to%20buy%20it%20and%20that%20we%20should%20be%20intentional%20about%20every%20dollar%20spent%20because%20money%20is%20a%20resource%20that%20should%20not%20be%20wasted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWatching%20her%20practice%20that%20habit%20over%20the%20years%20left%20a%20big%20impression%20on%20me.%20It%20helped%20me%20become%20more%20intentional%20about%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Getting%20the%20most%20out%20of%20compound%20interest%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20mother's%20first%20grandchild%20was%20born%2C%20she%20gave%20her%20parents%20money%20and%20asked%20them%20to%20open%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Ehigh-yield%20savings%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20my%20niece's%20name%20so%20the%20money%20would%20grow%20over%20time%20and%20provide%20a%20safety%20net%20for%20her.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20my%20mother%20would%20continue%20to%20add%20money%20to%20the%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20tradition%20she%20kept%20with%20her%20other%20grandkids%20while%20she%20was%20alive%20and%20healthy.%20Today%2C%20I%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-are-the-best-investment-apps%5C%22%3Einvestment%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20my%20kids%20as%20they%20provide%20a%20better%20opportunity%20for%20interest%20to%20compound%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20The%20importance%20of%20having%20life%20insurance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mother%20used%20to%20openly%20share%20that%20she%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-life-insurance-companies%5C%22%3Elife%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20policies%2C%20a%20taboo%20topic%20in%20our%20Cameroonian%20culture.%20When%20I%20asked%20her%20questions%20about%20it%2C%20she%20let%20me%20know%20that%20it%20was%20an%20important%20financial%20tool%20to%20have%20as%20it%20helped%20provide%20financial%20relief%20to%20your%20loved%20ones%20in%20the%20event%20of%20your%20passing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20my%20mother%20never%20explicitly%20advised%20me%20to%20get%20life%20insurance%2C%20I%20have%20had%20life%20insurance%20outside%20what%20is%20provided%20at%20work%20since%20my%20early%2020s%2C%20years%20before%20I%20started%20my%20own%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20f